result.name: Nan Viet Restaurant

reviews.text: Good food service especially management could be more friendly. Food and restaurant experience are just better in a pleasant environment. If you look miserable and act miserable it already makes the meal a little less enjoyable.
So so food, so called Vietnam food with bad attitude staff
Noodle soup were serve not hot. Not @ good place for Pho.

Vietnamese restaurants in Hong Kong are not considered many. For the few that I've tried, this is comparably average. The pork neck dish was a little too chewy for me and the rice was too dry. But the other side dishes were ok. They have the Vietnamese drip coffee which was a better end to my meal.

Service was quick enough for a busy lunch. Like most restaurants in Hong Kong, space is an issue. If you're alone, with two or three extra appetisers, it's tough to fit all on to your table which you had to share with another single patron.
Average price for Pho. A lot of seat provided.
